## Code of Conduct

Please review and adhere to our [Code of Conduct](CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) to ensure a positive and inclusive environment for everyone.

## How Can I Contribute?

### Reporting Bugs

If you encounter any bugs or issues, please [open an issue](https://github.com/coolusaHD/countdown-to-specific-date/issues) and provide detailed information about the problem. Include steps to reproduce, expected behavior, and any relevant error messages.

### Suggesting Enhancements

We welcome suggestions for new features or improvements. Please [open an issue](https://github.com/coolusaHD/countdown-to-specific-date/issues) and describe your idea or enhancement request. Be sure to provide as much detail as possible.

### Pull Requests

We encourage you to contribute to this project by submitting pull requests. To do so, follow these steps:

1. Fork the repository and create your branch from `main`.
2. Make your changes and ensure they follow the project's coding conventions.
3. Write clear and concise commit messages.
4. Test your changes thoroughly.
5. Submit a pull request, explaining the changes you made and why they should be merged.

We will review your pull request and provide feedback as soon as possible.

## Styleguides

Please follow the project's coding style and conventions when making contributions. This includes code formatting, naming conventions, and documentation guidelines. Refer to the project's documentation or `CONTRIBUTING` for specific guidelines.

## License

By contributing to this project, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the [LICENSE](LICENSE) file of the project.
